<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 19 at 4:53PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...SNOW SHOWERS INCREASING COVERAGE AND INTENSITY THIS EVENING
WILL REQUIRE CAUTIOUS TRAVEL...
WEATHER...
* Snow showers will increase coverage and intensity as strong
cold front crosses the Tri Cities, Thumb, and Flint regions this
evening.
* Snow accumulations of up to 1 inch are expected between 5 PM
and 8 PM.
* Southwest to west wind gusting around 30 mph.
IMPACTS...
* Rapid reduction of visibility to near a quarter mile in spots
with rapid fluctuations.
* Untreated roads quickly become snow covered, particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the variable
driving conditions by slowing down and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
